    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="989"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d989">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 989<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clayton</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d989fn1">Sent to the Secretary of State at
                        Babelsberg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-24">July 24,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>115. (For <persName corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName>.)</p>
                <p>For your information and with reference Department’s 56 of July 18,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d989fn2">
                        <ref target="#d984">Document No. 984</ref>.</note> Bucharest reports Soviets
                    now demand German bank stocks in Rumania.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
